2014 Statistics by Year: 1919 \u2013 2016 | publisher=[[Massachusetts Secretary of the Commonwealth]] | access-date=July 5, 2019}}\n* [[Massachusetts ballot measures, 1980]]:\n** 1. {{Aye}} Prohibit discrimination against handicapped persons\n** 2. {{Aye}} [[Proposition 2\u00bd]]\n** 3. {{Nay}} Limiting state and local taxes; increase state share of education costs\n** 4. {{Aye}} Increase salaries of certain state officials\n** 5. {{Aye}} Restrict state authority to place certain costs on cities and towns\n** 6. {{Nay}} Change legislative voting procedure for emergency laws\n* [[Massachusetts ballot measures, 2002]]:\n** 1. {{Nay}} Eliminating State Personal Income Tax\n** 2. {{Aye}} [[Massachusetts English Language Education in Public Schools Initiative]]\n** 3. {{Nay}} Taxpayer Funding for Political Campaigns\n* Massachusetts ballot measures, 2004:\n** ''none''\n* [[Massachusetts ballot measures, 2006]]:\n** 1. {{Nay}} Sale of Wine by Food Stores\n** 2. {{Nay}} Nomination of Candidates for Public Office\n** 3. {{Nay}} Family Child Care Providers\n* [[Massachusetts ballot measures, 2008]]:\n** 1. {{Nay}} [[Massachusetts State Income Tax Repeal]]\n** 2. {{Aye}} [[Massachusetts Sensible Marijuana Policy]]\n** 3. {{Aye}} [[Massachusetts Greyhound Protection Act]]\n* [[Massachusetts ballot measures, 2010]]:\n** 1. {{Aye}} [[Massachusetts No Sales Tax for Alcohol Initiative]]\n** 2. {{Nay}} [[Massachusetts Comprehensive Permits and Regional Planning Initiative]]\n** 3. {{Nay}} [[Massachusetts Sales Tax Relief Act]]\n* [[Massachusetts ballot measures, 2012]]:\n** 1. {{Aye}} [[Massachusetts Right to Repair Initiative]]\n** 2. {{Nay}} [[Massachusetts Death with Dignity Initiative]]\n** 3. {{Aye}} [[Massachusetts Medical Marijuana Initiative]]\n* [[Massachusetts ballot measures, 2014]]:\n** 1. {{Aye}} [[Massachusetts Automatic Gas Tax Increase Repeal Initiative]]\n** 2. {{Nay}} [[Massachusetts Expansion of Bottle Deposits Initiative]]\n** 3. {{Nay}} [[Massachusetts Casino R