e]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|1807\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|[[1807 Massachusetts's 12th congressional district special election|1807 12th congressional district special election]]\n|-\n|1808\n|\n|\n|[[1808 United States House of Representatives elections in Massachusetts|1808 House]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|[[1808 Massachusetts's 2nd congressional district special election|1808  2nd congressional district special election]]\n|-\n|1809\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|}\n\n=== 1810s ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Massachusetts Elections of the 1800s\n!\n! colspan=\"3\" |Federal Elections\n! colspan=\"5\" |State Elections\n!Local Elections\n!Special Elections\n|-\n!\n!Presidential\n!Senate\n!House of Rep.\n!Governor\n!State Senate\n!State House of Reps\n!Governors. Council\n!Ballot Measures\n!\n!\n|-\n|1800\n|\n|\n| rowspan=\"2\" |\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|1801\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|1802\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|1803\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|1804\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|1805\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|1806\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|1807\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|1808\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|1809\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|}\n\n=== 1810 ===\n* [[1810\u20131811 United States House of Representatives elections in Massachusetts]]\n* [[1810 Massachusetts's 10th congressional district special election]] ([[Joseph Allen (congressman)|Joseph Allen]])\n* [[1810 Massachusetts's 11th congressional district special election]] ([[Abijah Bigelow]])\n\n=== 1811 ===\n* [[1811 Massachusetts's 4th congressional district special election]] ([[William M. Richardson]])\n\n=== 1812 ===\n* [[1812\u20131813 United States House of Representatives elections in Massachusetts]]\n* [[1812 Massachusetts's 17th congressional district special election]] ([[Francis Carr (District of Maine politician)|Francis Carr]])\n\n=== 1814 ===\n* [[1814\u20131815 United States House of Representatives elections in Massac