{"title_page": "2020\u201321 Tulsa Golden Hurricane men's basketball team", "text_new": "{{short description|University of Tulsa NCAA team}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n  |mode=Basketball\n  |year=2020\u201321\n  |prev_year=2019\u201320\n  |next_year=2021\u201322\n  |team=Tulsa Golden Hurricane\n  |image=Tulsa Golden Hurricane wordmark.svg\n  |image_size=175\n  |conference=American Athletic Conference\n  |division=\n  |short_conf=AAC\n  |CoachRank=\n  |APRank=\n  |record=\n  |conf_record=\n  |head_coach=[[Frank Haith]]\n  |hc_year = 7th\n  |asst_coach1=[[Jerry Wainwright]]\n  |asst_coach2=Kwanza Johnson\n  |asst_coach3=[[Shea Seals]]\n  |stadium=[[Reynolds Center]]\n  |champion=\n}}\n{{2020\u201321 American Athletic Conference men's basketball standings}}\nThe '''2020\u201321 Tulsa Golden Hurricane men's basketball team''' will represent the [[University of Tulsa]] during the [[2020\u201321 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. The Golden Hurricane, led by seventh-year head coach [[Frank Haith]], plays their home games at the [[Reynolds Center]] in [[Tulsa, Oklahoma]] as members of the [[American Athletic Conference]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.collegesportsmadness.com/article/17640|title=#105 Tulsa Men's Basketball 2019\u20132020 Preview|website=www.collegesportsmadness.com|language=en|access-date=2019-12-02}}</ref>\n\n==Previous season==\nThe [[2019\u201320 Tulsa Golden Hurricane men's basketball team|Golden Hurricane]] finished the [[2019\u201320 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2019\u201320 season]] 21\u201310, 13\u20135 in [[2019\u201320 American Athletic Conference men's basketball season|AAC play]] to finish in a tie for first place and winning a share of the regular season title. Coach Haith would go on to be honored as [[American Athletic Conference Men's Basketball Coach of the Year]] for the season. They entered as the No. 3 seed in the [[2020 American Athletic Conference Men's Basketball Tournament|AAC Tournament]], which was ultimately cancelled due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]].\n\n==Offseason==\n===Departures===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n! Name !! Number !! Pos. !! Height !! Weight !! Year !! Hometown !! class=\"unsortable\" | Reason for departure\n|-\n| Martins Igbanu || 1 || F || 6'8\" || 235 || {{sort|4|Senior}} || [[Lagos|Lagos, Nigeria]] || Graduated\n|-\n| Isaiah Hill || 4 || G || 6'0\" || 165 || {{sort|1|Freshman}} || [[Bakersfield, California|Bakersfield, CA]] || Transferred to [[Fresno State Bulldogs men's basketball|Fresno State]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Moore |first1=Jackson |title=Bakersfield star Isaiah Hill transferring home to Fresno State |url=https://247sports.com/college/fresno-state/Article/Bakersfield-star-Isaiah-Hill-transferring-home-to-Fresno-State-basketball-145590191/ |website=247sports.com |accessdate=11 Apr 2020 |date=31 Mar 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Lawson Korita || 5 || G || 6'5\" || 205 || {{sort|4|Senior}} || [[Little Rock, Arkansas|Little Rock, AR]] || Graduated\n|-\n| Reggie Jones || 22 || G || 6'6\" || 210 || {{sort|3|Sophomore}} || [[Marion, Indiana|Marion, IN]] || Transferred to [[Ball State Cardinals men's basketball|Ball State]].<ref>{{cite news |author=Tribune sports staff |title=Ball State men's basketball adds 2 transfers |url=https://www.kokomotribune.com/sports/ball-state-mens-basketball-adds-2-transfers/article_75c76822-7f59-11ea-b8cd-23fbad025f12.html |accessdate=15 Apr 2020 |work=[[Kokomo Tribune]] |date=20 Apr 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Zeke Moore (basketball)|Zeke Moore]] || 23 || G || 6'7\" || 210 || {{sort|2.5|RS Sophomore}} || [[St. Louis|St. Louis, MO]] || Transferred to [[SIU Edwardsville Cougars men's basketball|SIU Edwardsville]] (mid-season).<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hines |first1=Kelly |title=TU guard Moore leaving men's basketball program |url=https://www.tulsaworld.com/sports/college/tu/tu-guard-moore-leaving-men-s-basketball-program/article_754b1028-8101-5c8e-b010-89ec19e240b6.html |accessdate